!! Node properties

|!Property |!Type |!Default |!Notes |
|`label` |string | |Display text below node |
|`color` |color | |Background color |
|`fontColor` |color |auto |Text color (auto-derived from background contrast) |
|`borderColor` |color | |Border color |
|`borderWidth` |number |1 |Border thickness |
|`size` |number |25 |Node radius (Cytoscape renders at size × 2) |
|`shape` |enum |dot |`dot` / `box` / `ellipse` / `circle` / `diamond` / `triangle` / `star` / `hexagon` / `database` |
|`fixed` |boolean |false |Lock node position (prevent dragging) |
|`image` |image | |Background image |
|`cluster` |string | |Cytoscape compound parent ID for static grouping (see ''Clusters'' section) |

!! Edge properties

|!Property |!Type |!Default |!Notes |
|`label` |string | |Text on edge (auto-rotated to follow edge direction) |
|`color` |color | |Line color + arrow color |
|`width` |number |1 |Line thickness |
|`arrows` |enum |to |`no` / `to` / `from` / `middle` (supports multiple, comma-separated) |
|`stroke` |enum |solid |`solid` / `dashed` / `dotted` |
|`hidden` |boolean |false |Hide edge |

!! Graph properties

|!Property |!Type |!Default |!Notes |
|`physics` |boolean |true |Enable COSE physics layout |
|`hierarchy` |boolean |false |Hierarchical layout (uses breadthfirst) |
|`hierarchyDirection` |enum |UD |`UD` / `DU` / `LR` / `RL` |
|`zoom` |boolean |true |Enable mouse wheel zoom |
|`zoomSpeed` |number |1 |Zoom sensitivity (0–10) |
|`navigation` |boolean |true |Enable panning |
|`nodeColor` |color | |Default node color for all nodes |
|`edgeColor` |color | |Default edge color for all edges |
|`fontColor` |color | |Default text color for labels |
|`clusterData` |string | |Tiddler path for interactive cluster config (JSON). Each graph can use its own tiddler. |

!! Clusters

Clusters are named visual groups stored in a JSON config tiddler. They are ''not'' TiddlyWiki tiddlers — they exist only as entries in the config.

!!! Enabling interactive clusters

Set `clusterData` on `<$properties $for="graph">` pointing to a config tiddler:

```
<$graph>
<$properties $for="graph" clusterData="$:/config/my-app/clusters">
  ...
</$properties>
</$graph>
```

Each graph can point to its own tiddler for independent clusters, or share a tiddler for synchronized clusters.

!!! Config tiddler format

```json
{
  "clusters": {
    "Cluster #1": { "label": "Cluster #1", "color": "#2B7CE9" },
    "Team B": { "label": "Team B", "color": null, "parent": "Cluster #1" }
  },
  "assignments": {
    "tiddler-id-1": "Cluster #1",
    "tiddler-id-2": "Cluster #1",
    "tiddler-id-3": "Team B"
  }
}
```

|!Field |!Purpose |
|`clusters` |Named cluster definitions with label, color, and optional parent (for nesting) |
|`assignments` |Maps node IDs (tiddler titles) to cluster names |
|`clusters.*.color` |Border and background tint color (`null` for default gray) |
|`clusters.*.parent` |Name of parent cluster (for nested clusters) |

!!! Interaction gestures

|!Gesture |!Effect |
|Drag node onto node |Auto-creates cluster containing both (named "Cluster #N") |
|Drag node onto cluster |Adds node to existing cluster |
|Drag node onto sibling in cluster |Adds to the same cluster |
|Drag node 200+ px from grab point |Removes node from cluster |
|Double-click cluster label |Opens inline rename + color picker |
|Drag cluster onto cluster |Nests the dragged cluster inside the target |
|Remove all members |Cluster auto-deletes |

!!! Visual feedback

When dragging a node inside a cluster:

* ''< 50% of ejection distance'' — normal cluster border
* ''50–85%'' — border turns orange, stays dashed
* ''> 85%'' — border turns solid red, thickens
* ''On drop'' — border resets to normal

!!! Static clusters (no interaction)

For hardcoded grouping without `clusterData`, set `cluster` directly on `<$node>`. The container node ID must use the `__cluster__` prefix:

```
<$node $tiddler="__cluster__GroupName" label="Group Name"/>
<$node $tiddler="ChildA" label="A" cluster="__cluster__GroupName"/>
```

!! Shape mapping

|!tw-graph value |!Cytoscape shape |
|`dot` (default) |`ellipse` |
|`circle` |`ellipse` |
|`ellipse` |`ellipse` |
|`box` |`rectangle` |
|`square` |`rectangle` |
|`diamond` |`diamond` |
|`triangle` |`triangle` |
|`star` |`star` |
|`hexagon` |`hexagon` |
|`database` |`barrel` |

!! Engine selection

Set `$:/config/flibbles/graph/engine` to `Cytoscape` or use ControlPanel > Settings > Graph Engine.

Both engines can coexist — switching back to `Vis-Network` works without any changes to graph markup. Cluster-specific features (`cluster` attribute, `clusterData` property) are silently ignored by vis-network.

